The leader of the Al Jama-ah party in parliament, Ganief Hendricks, has called for Muslim marriages to be dignified with marriage certificates to end the huge outcry from many Muslims who struggled to enjoy their marriage rights because their unions were not recognised in law. He also called for the release on parole of three members of the People Against Gangsterism and Drugs (Pagad) who had been imprisoned for years and not considered for parole although they qualified for it two years ago in Cape Town. The prisoners were not even set free during the recent parole release implemented by...